Here are the simplified results (we assume all letters denote positive quantities so that \(\sqrt{p^2}=p\), \(\sqrt[q]{q^4}=q^2\), etc.):

a)  
\[
\frac{\sqrt{108\,p^5\,q^2}}{\sqrt{3\,p^3\,q^6}}
=\sqrt{\frac{108}{3}\,\frac{p^5}{p^3}\,\frac{q^2}{q^6}}
=\sqrt{36\,p^2\,q^{-4}}
=6\,\frac{p}{q^2}.
\]

b)  
\[
\frac{\sqrt[3]{-16\,a^4\,b^{-2}}}{\sqrt[3]{2\,a^{-2}\,b}}
=\sqrt[3]{\frac{-16}{2}\,\frac{a^4}{a^{-2}}\,\frac{b^{-2}}{b}}
=\sqrt[3]{-8\,a^6\,b^{-3}}
